  "response_text": "A white, eye-chart-like background fills the screen, with faint grey measuring numbers along the sides. Large tan letters at the top and smaller rows below first look like a vision test with random letters, then the middle rows resolve into the words “LENS” and “CRAFTERS” in bold black type.\n\nA woman with shoulder-length dark hair appears on the left, wearing narrow rectangular eyeglasses, a dark blouse, and a small pendant necklace. She faces forward with a calm, slight smile. Behind her, the LensCrafters words remain large on the white background. She tilts her head and smiles a little more, showing off the glasses, then moves out of view.\n\nThe white background returns to shifting eye-chart letters. A man wearing glasses, a burgundy long-sleeved shirt, dark trousers, and dark shoes bounds in from the right. He is frozen in a joyful, exaggerated leap with one arm raised high and his legs stretched wide, as if jumping across the screen. Behind him, large text forms into “HAPPINESS GUARANTEE,” with “HAPPINESS” in black and “GUARANTEE” in tan. The man continues across the words, smiling while suspended in the air.\n\nLarge tan numerals begin to appear, changing into “30,” with “DAYS” beneath in black. A blonde woman with a short, side-swept haircut fills the right side in close-up. She wears dark oval or rectangular eyeglasses and looks directly forward with a soft smile. The “30 DAYS” text sits clearly to her left on the white background, visually matching the audio context about having 30 days to wear the glasses.\n\nThe scene shifts to a man with short spiky hair wearing a dark blazer over a blue shirt. He stands against the same white background, wearing thin eyeglasses and looking forward with a faint smile. In the far upper left, a tiny full-body figure of a woman in a dark patterned dress stands like a miniature person within the graphic space. Along the bottom, large tan and black letters gradually resolve into “FIRST PAIR.” The man touches his glasses near the temples, as if considering or trying them on, then moves partly out of view.\n\nHe dips down and rises back into the center, now adjusting a different pair of darker rectangular glasses with both hands. The bottom text changes to “NEW PAIR.” He finishes settling the new glasses on his face and looks forward, suggesting an exchange from one pair to another.\n\nA woman with short light-brown hair and eyeglasses appears centered, holding a rectangular printed image in both hands. The image shows the front of a LensCrafters store, with a black sign reading “LENSCRAFTERS” above a bright storefront interior. She holds the picture up so it covers the lower half of her face, leaving her eyes visible over the top edge; then she lowers her gaze slightly behind it.\n\nThe screen changes to a simple white background with the black “LensCrafters” logo centered. Finally, a large offer appears: small grey text at the top reads “ALL GLASSES,” and huge tan text fills most of the screen: “$100 OFF.” Fine-print text runs along the bottom but is too small to read clearly.",
